                                                    US STOCKS-Wall St opens lower as Amazon weighs on tech stocks
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    9:56 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


* Amazon (AMZN) falls after quarterly profit plunges. * Starbucks (SBUX), Mattel (MAT) lower after posting results. * Q2 GDP up 2.6 pct vs 1.2 pct rise in Q1. * Indexes down: Dow 0.04 pct, S&P 0.18 pct, Nasdaq 0.51 pct. By Tanya Agrawal. U.S. stock indexes opened lower on Friday as Amazon's (AMZN) profit miss spooked investors and dragged down shares of other technology companies.

















                                                    US STOCKS-Wall St set to open lower as Amazon weighs on tech stocks
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    9:02 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


* Amazon (AMZN) falls after quarterly profit plunges. * Starbucks (SBUX), Mattel (MAT) lower after posting results. * Q2 GDP up 2.6 pct vs 1.2 pct rise in Q1. * Futures down: Dow 31 pts, S&P 5.5 pts, Nasdaq 40.5 pts. By Tanya Agrawal. U.S. stock indexes looked set to open lower on Friday as Amazon's (AMZN) profit miss took a toll on technology shares.

















                                                    A quarter of S&P 500's 2017 climb due to five stocks (yes, those five)
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    8:11 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


The tech sector has provided more than 40% of the S&P 500' s advance. Throughout 2017, there's one acronym that investors have in particular been sinking their teeth into: FAANG. The term stands for a quintet of the market's most pronounced highfliers: Facebook Inc. (FB), Apple Inc. (AAPL), Amazon.com Inc. (AMZN), Netflix Inc. (NFLX), and Alphabet, the parent company of Google.

















                                                    US STOCKS-Futures lower as tech stocks take a beating
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    7:33 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


* Futures down: Dow 26 pts, S&P 7.75 pts, Nasdaq 46.5 pts. U.S. stock index futures were lower on Friday as Amazon's (AMZN) profit miss took a toll on technology shares. * Amazon's (AMZN) shares were down 2.96 percent in premarket trading after it reported a 77 percent drop in profit as its rapid and costly expansion into new shopping categories and countries showed no sign of slowing.

















                                                    Altice's group results offset SFR's profit decline in second quarter
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    4:30 PM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


Telecoms and cable group Altice reported a surge of its second-quarter core operating profit on Thursday, offsetting the profit decline of its number one listed division SFR Group.

















                                                    Tech shares fall 1%, weighing on broader market; Apple and Alphabet both tumble
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    1:39 PM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


The largest exchange-traded fund to track the technology sector fell on Thursday, erasing an earlier gain and leading the broader market lower. The Technology Select Sector SPDR ETF (XLK) fell 1.1% in afternoon trading, dropping to$ 57.10. Earlier, it had risen as high as $58.20, largely on the back of positive results out of Facebook Inc..













						                            
			                                Netflix shares are down more than 4%
			                            


			                                MarketWatch – 
			                                1:31 PM ET 07/27/2017
			                            












						                            
			                                Shares of Netflix are down more than 2%
			                            


			                                MarketWatch – 
			                                12:40 PM ET 07/27/2017
			                            
















                                                    Hollywood fighting Netflix is like yelling at an oncoming tsunami
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    12:29 PM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


Continuing criticism of Netflix's (NFLX) film approach, GQ asked filmmakers about the streaming giant's presence in the industry. Hollywood filmmakers may not agree with Netflix's (NFLX) method of releasing films, but they're unlikely to fully turn their back on the streaming giant. In a Q&A piece in its August issue, GQ magazine asked some of Hollywood's most prominent filmmakers about the experience of making films in 2017. Naturally, the conversation turned to industry disrupter...

















                                                    Bullish analyst says Netflix could reach $30 EPS over time
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    11:19 AM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


MKM Partners analyst Rob Sanderson put out a bullish note on Netflix Inc. (NFLX) on Thursday, raising his 12- month price target on the streaming giant to $230 from $195. That represents a 23% premium to current trading levels. Sanderson also said his model suggests that Netflix (NFLX) hitting earnings of $30 per share is possible over time. "While we look to our $12 EPS power in 2021 as our valuation benchmark, we think there is a much larger opportunity over time," Sanderson wrote.

















                                                    Comcast 2nd-qtr results top estimates on film, theme parks growth
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    9:30 AM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


Comcast Corp (CMCSA) on Thursday reported quarterly results that topped analysts' estimates on higher revenue in its filmed entertainment and theme parks businesses, even as the No. 1 U.S. cable operator lost more video subscribers. Comcast's (CMCSA) shares rose 2 percent to $40.16 in early trading.

















                                                    Comcast results top estimates on film, theme parks growth
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    6:00 AM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


Comcast Corp's (CMCSA) quarterly results topped Wall Street analysts' estimates on higher revenue in its filmed entertainment and theme parks businesses, even as the No. 1 U.S. cable operator lost video subscribers. Net income attributable to Comcast (CMCSA) rose 23.9 percent to $2.51 billion, or 52 cents a share, during the company's second quarter ended June 30, up from $2.03 billion, or 41 cents a share.

















                                                    Singapore slings? Taking on Alibaba, Amazon launches Prime Now in the city state
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    8:58 PM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


Amazon.com Inc (AMZN) launched its two-hour delivery service in Singapore on Thursday, marking the e-commerce giant's push into populous Southeast Asia and its first head-on battle with its Chinese rival, Alibaba Group Holding (BABA). While Amazon (AMZN) does deliver to Singapore, higher-end services had not been available, such as Prime services which include access to the company's video-streaming service.

















                                                    'Dunkirk' director Christopher Nolan rips Netflix, praises Amazon
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    2:34 PM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


The' Dark Knight' director criticized Netflix (NFLX) for its' bizarre aversion to supporting theatrical films'. On the eve of premiering his Warner Bros. World War II epic, "Dunkirk," director Christopher Nolan criticized streaming service Netflix (NFLX) for its "bizarre aversion to supporting theatrical films" and called its film policies "mindless."













						                            
